					<head>Commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>The commentary of Daṿid ben Bo῾az on the book of Exodus (fragments).</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="ara" otherLangs="he">Arabic, Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="108v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Daṿid ben Bo῾az </persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he">דוד בן בועז</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>A part of an Arabic commentary on Exodus, viz. chpaters 25:1-33:13, ascribed to Daṿid ben Bo῾az.</p>
								<p>Imperfect at the end.</p>
								<p>Each pericope is divided in to a number of section marked as ؤصل, which comprise of chapters: 25:1-9, 10-22, 23-30, 31-40; 26:1-6, 7-14, 15-30, 31-37; 27:1-8, 9-19, 20-21; 28:1-5, 6-14, 15-30, 31-35, 36-38, 39, 40, 41-43; 29:1-37, 38-46; 30:1-10, 11-16, 17-21, 22-33, 34-38; 31:1-11, 12-17; 31:18-32:6; 32:7-14, 15-29; [30-35 are wanting]; 33:1-11, 12-23.</p>
								<p>The division into smaller section agrees with parashiyot petuḥot or setumot of the printed text.</p>
								<p>In each section the Arabic translation is prefixed.</p>
								<p>Of the Hebrew text only the opening words of each verse are given.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
